description:
Giving Nature A Voice - Season 1, Episode 3: The African Fish Eagle - Defying Danger in Naivasha | Nature Documentary

Watch 'Giving Nature A Voice - Season 1, Episode 4' here: https://youtu.be/iNT9zNM3WJo
 
Lake Naivasha has the largest population of African fish eagles in the world, despite that fact that Naivasha city has grown to a million people and hosts one of the main export earners of Kenya  the flower industry. Although the lake is under severe pressure, a Kenyan born raptor scientist Dr. Munir Virani tries to explain why the eagles are doing so well and how to save their precious home. Nonetheless, the threats faced by Lake Naivasha from invasive species introduced into the lake are great and the film also profiles the people working to find a solution to the lakes environmental crisis.

Free Documentary is dedicated to bring high-class documentaries to you on youtube for free. With the latest camera equipment used by well-known filmmakers working for famous production studios. You will see fascinating shots from the deep seas and up in the air, capturing great stories and pictures from everything our beautiful and interesting planet has to offer. 

Enjoy stories about nature, wildlife, culture, people, history and more to come.
